headline: Sysco (SYY): Assessing Valuation After a Year of Negative Returns Despite Rising Earnings
summary: Sysco (SYY) has quietly lagged the broader market this year, with the stock down about 4% over the past year even as revenue and earnings keep grinding higher, which creates an interesting setup. See our latest analysis for Sysco. At around $74.34, the recent 1 week share price uptick has not yet offset the 3 month slide. The 1 year total shareholder return of roughly negative 4.5% suggests momentum has been fading rather than accelerating. If Sysco has you rethinking where stable cash flows...
